author: @aaravbhatt760
text: Well, I got the book when I was 14. I understood the basics about how it worked and it gave me a good understanding of calculus (which was new to me at the time - I have got much better at it now). However, I quickly moved to tensorflow, which seemed easier. Now, I am rereading the book again to get a deeper knowledge of neural networks (I have just turned 16 now). It would be nice to see a follow-up book about convolutional neural networks, graph neural networks and and transformers.

author: @g4anode
text: My NNFS book was left in the rain for a whole night (got delivered super late in the evening, which I didn't notice). I found out the book was remarkably resistant to water, with pages being only somewhat distorted after drying for a week. After keeping it under a weight for a while (please don't remind me how long it's been since release, I'm still procrastinating lol) it all but straightened out and you could never tell it got wet.  You reminded me of this when you mention shipping straight up losing packages haha.

author: @TheRysiu120
text: The nnfs series as you say does not compare to anything else available on this platform and I understand that you have a lot of new projects worthy of realization and I would not for anything want you to burn out because it would be an irreparable loss. However if you say it takes 2 weeks then maybe you could do it so that you put one episode maybe once every 3 - 4 months, it sounds doable. Of course I know that you probably will not change your way of uploading videos and in no way will I try to convince you to do so, but I just loved these videos for the fact that I can learn from them and I feel that by the time this series is over I will have graduated :D First of all, keep up the good work and stay true to your vision. Can I at least ask when approximately the next episode will come out, will it be more like 3 months, half a year or a year? And how many episodes by default do you plan for this series to have?

author: @CitizensCommunity
text: The book is an amazing product at a great price, that was clearly made by people who care. The videos have been amazing and helped me understand a point I was stuck on. I am going from not knowing how to program and jumping to NNs, your book has been what has made that possible. While other videos are able to help with a deeper understanding of some parts, your videos have been the best way to get the information. Complaints that the videos are not released sooner are just a demonstration of how valuable people are finding the videos, and the loss they feel when they do not have the next one. Please do not undervalue the importance these videos have, but you are also not a youtube slave and need to take care of yourself and your goals as well.
